Nigeria is one of 21 countries invited to attend the inaugural UK-Africa Investment Summit in London. Nigeria's delegation will be headed by President Muhammadu Buhari where they will engage investors and meet with British Prime Minister, Boris Johnson. Nigeria's President will also be hosted by the Duke and Duchess of Cambridge. Kayode Akidele, Partner at TIA Capital joins CNBC Africa to explore ways to strengthen trade ties between the U.K and Nigeria and other business news making the rounds in Nigeria....